  "original_title": "\u0db8\u0dad\u0dca\u0daf\u0dca\u200d\u0dbb\u0dc0\u0dca\u200d\u0dba \u0da2\u0dcf\u0dc0\u0dcf\u0dbb\u0db8\u0dd9\u0db1\u0dca \u0db8\u0dd2\u0dbd\u0daf\u0dd3 \u0d9c\u0dad\u0dca \u0d9a\u0ddd\u0da7\u0dd2 02\u0d9a \u0db1\u0dd2\u0dc0\u0dcf\u0dc3 02\u0d9a\u0dca \u0dbb\u0da2\u0dba\u0da7",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "02 houses worth 02 crores bought from drug trafficking to the government",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The Criminal Investigation Department today (20th) said that two houses worth nearly two crore rupees, which were bought by a husband and wife involved in the drug trade of a large-scale drug trafficker hiding abroad, Ratmalana Kudu Anju, were taken over from the government by the government. Or says Property Investigation Division.",
        "In 2021, in the case of a husband and wife who were arrested with 80 grams of drugs by the Moratumulla police, during the initial investigations conducted by the Criminal Investigation Department's Illegal Assets or Investigation Division, two plots of land with two houses worth nearly two crores of rupees were bought in Fernando Mawatha, Moratuwa, through the said drug trade. It was discovered that a stock of gold goods weighing about 300 pounds, worth nearly 3 crore rupees, a lorry, a three-wheeler and a motorcycle had been purchased, and the police said that the property was banned under the Money Laundering Act and a lengthy investigation was carried out.",
        "In this regard, after filing a case in the Moratuwa Magistrate's Court by the Illegal Assets or Investigation Division, the woman was released from the couple on bail.",
        "Then in relation to that property, the Property or Assets Investigation Division of the Panadura Western Provincial High Court issued orders to freeze the two houses in Fernando Mawatha, Moratumulla, and take them over to the government in accordance with the provisions of the Money Laundering Prevention Act No. 5 of 2006 amended by the Act No. 40 of 2011. had",
        "As the recipient of the Money Laundering Act, the Moratuwa Divisional Secretary Mrs. Ishanka D K Udawatta came to those places with the officers of the Criminal Investigation Department's Illegal Assets or Property Investigation Division and handed over the relevant property to the government.",
        "The police added that the heavy gold stock of 300 families, which is said to have been bought by the suspected husband and wife through drug trafficking, worth about three crore rupees, has been forwarded to the Gems and Jewelery Authority for valuation.",
        "On the advice of the Director of the Criminal Investigation Department, DIG Prasad Ranasinghe, investigations are being carried out on the advice of the Illegal Assets or Property Investigation Division, Senior Superintendent of Police Laksiri Gital."
      ],
